    "name": "LED Name Badge API",
    "description": "# LED Name Badge API\n\nThis API controls an LED name badge display using Flask. It allows you to display custom text, retrieve available predefined icons, and show a summary message on the LED badge.\n\n## Base URL\n`http://localhost:5001`\n\n## Features\n- **Display Custom Text**: Send any text to be displayed on the LED badge\n- **Get Predefined Icons**: Retrieve a list of available icons that can be used in text (format: `:icon_name:`)\n- **Display Summary**: Show a predefined summary message on the LED badge\n\n## Usage Notes\n- The API uses the `lednamebadge` Python library to communicate with the LED badge hardware\n- Icons can be embedded in text using the format `:icon_name:` (e.g., `:star:`, `:heart:`)\n- All POST endpoints return status 200 on success\n- The LED badge must be connected to the system running the API",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
